item.content:encoded:
In addition to Friday night's <a href="http://kicksnarehat.wordpress.com/2012/06/01/june-8-double-duty-hillbilly-holiday-weisstronauts-at-moes-lounge/">double-header</a>, I'll be at Toad Sunday night with John Powhida International Airport. Set time is 9pm, and there's no cover charge!

<a href="http://www.songkick.com/concerts/13018498">Event details at SongKick</a>

&nbsp;

Hot off the heals of our sold-out release for <a href="http://johnpowhidainternationalairport.bandcamp.com/album/airport-life">Airport Life</a> at the Lizard Lounge, John Powhida International Airport is landing at Atwoods Tavern this Friday, opening for our friends The Tim Gearan Band. We're gonna play the entire record again, so if you missed it last time c'mon out! JPX starts at 10, with TGB at 11.

<a href="https://www.songkick.com/events/21155343">Details on Songkick</a>

&nbsp;

Double-duty <a href="https://www.songkick.com/concerts/26721049" target="_blank">this Saturday at Sally O'Brien's</a> with The Weisstronauts and John Powhida International Airport (w/ special guest Jimmy Z on bass). <a href="https://biggiantmusic.bandcamp.com/" target="_blank">Big Giant</a> opens, only $5 cover.

[bandcamp width=350 height=470 album=2830744941 size=large bgcol=333333 linkcol=0f91ff tracklist=false track=460800019]

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Another double-duty Saturday night as the John Powhida Regional Landing Strip* and HillBilly Holiday share the not-quite-a-stage at the Plough &amp; Stars. 10pm

Anything can happen at the Plough, and here's proof:

https://youtu.be/hb58YBBr0y4

&nbsp;

* A somewhat smaller version of the International Airport

&nbsp;

It's Double-Duty Tuesday -- two shows at Toad: 7:30 early show with Martha Bourne (x-Nash Satterfield), then 10pm with John Powhida International Airport. No cover charge!

[bandcamp width=100% height=42 album=2830744941 size=small bgcol=333333 linkcol=0f91ff track=1005925420]

&nbsp;

Three shows this weekend, starting Saturday with the Weisstronauts 18th Annual Holiday Jubilee, this year at <a href="http://www.atwoodstavern.com">Atwood's Tavern</a> w/ The I Want You. $5 donation, 3:30 showtime.

Sunday's secular celebrations include both Hillbilly Holiday and Amber Casares/Junky Love, each playing a couple sets at <a href="http://www.aeronautbrewing.com">Aeronaut Brewing Co</a>. No cover, 2 - 7pm (ish).

[bandcamp width=350 height=470 album=952631257 size=large bgcol=333333 linkcol=0f91ff tracklist=false track=4143120468]

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
